<BYLINE>By KERIN HOPE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> recalled all its ambassadors from European Common Market nations Tuesday and <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> expelled an Iranian envoy as the diplomatic battle grew over <PERSON> Ayatollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruhollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>'s death threats against author <PERSON> Salman </PERSON> <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>. In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said he supported the retaliatory moves by the European countries. However offensive <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>'s book, `` The Satanic Verses,'' may be to Moslems, `` inciting murder and offering rewards for its perpetration are deeply offensive to the norms of civilized behavior,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said. The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> does not have diplomatic relations with <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> noted existing economic sanctions against <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and said: `` I do n't know where we'll go from there.'' In <LOCATION> Ottawa </LOCATION>, Foreign Minister <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Clark </PERSON> said Tuesday that <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> is withdrawing its charge d'affaires from <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> for consultations on the death threats issue, but is leaving one diplomatic representative in <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s official <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> said <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s diplomatic recall was in response to Monday's decision by the 12 nations of the <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Community </ORGANIZATION> to withdraw their envoys from <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> for consultations Iranian parliament speaker <PERSON> Hashemi </PERSON> <PERSON> Rafsanjani </PERSON> called the <ORGANIZATION> EEC <