countries from which Iranian ambassadors were withdrawn, background. ADDS
byline. No pickup. ^By NEIL MacFARQUHAR</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> recalled all its ambassadors from Common Market countries today, a day after the 12 European countries recalled their envoys to protest <PERSON> Ayatollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>'s execution order against novelist <PERSON> Salman </PERSON> <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>. The move by the <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> was in direct reponse to the Common Market foreign ministers' decision in <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Belgium </LOCATION>, on Monday to recall their ambassadors from <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION>, the official <ORGANIZATION> Islamic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Republic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> reported. <ORGANIZATION> IRNA </ORGANIZATION> did not specify the countries from which the Iranian ambassadors were withdrawn and it was not immediately known in what Common Market countries <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> has maintained ambassadors. In <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>, for example, <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> has been represented by a charge d'affaires. <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> said in a statement that respect for <ORGANIZATION> Islam </ORGANIZATION> and its values will remain an inviolable principle in relations between <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> and other countries, <ORGANIZATION> IRNA </ORGANIZATION> said. The communique said that <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>'s week-old order for <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>'s death for blaspheming Islam with his book `` The Satanic Verses'' was a `` consensus judgement of all Moslem leaders throught the world,'' the agency reported The dispatch, monitored in <LOCATION> Nicosia </LOCATION>, said the <ORGANIZATION> Foreign </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> deplored the refusal of the European community to condemn the book and criticized the community's support for a work it said blasphemes Islam. <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> announced Monday it would withdraw all its diplomats from <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION> and request that <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> recall its representatives in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> had refused to accept <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>'s apology for offending Moslems with the book, affirming his call for Moslems to kill the naturalized Briton, who is reportedly in hiding under police guard. <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> stopped short of actually severing ties, while its partners in the Common Market said they would recall their envoys for consultations. Many Moslems say `` The Satanic Verses'' portrays the prophet <PERSON> Mohammed </PERSON>'s wives as prostitutes and suggests that he _ rather than God _ wrote the Koran, <ORGANIZATION> Islam </ORGANIZATION>'s holy book. The novel has been banned in <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Africa </LOCATION>. Publishers in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Greece </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Turkey </LOCATION> have canceled plans to publish it and it has been pulled from bookstore shelves in <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>. Many <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> bookstores have also removed the novel from display. The novel has also prompted Moslem protests around the world. In <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> earlier this month, seven people were killed in protests against it.
