<HEAD>Soccer Players, Fans Rescue Passengers of Sinking Ferry</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Players and spectators of a soccer match saved about 100 passengers from a sinking ferry in northeastern <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION>, witnesses and police said Tuesday. There were no injuries. The ferry was carrying more than double its sanctioned capacity, and sank near the banks of <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Karala </LOCATION> at <LOCATION> Mahasingh </LOCATION>, 110 miles northeast of <LOCATION> Dhaka </LOCATION> on Monday, they said. Most of the 22 players of a soccer match and hundreds of spectators who heard the screams of the passengers jumped into the river, witnesses said. They rescued women and children from the hull of the sinking ferry. Almost all male passengers already had reached safety. `` The passengers could survive as the ferry sank near the bank and it took 30 minutes to sink,'' a police officer said. Ferry accidents are common in <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION>. Officials estimate 900 people have died in about 60 such accidents in the past seven years.
