ture. In its appeal to the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Pavelic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> LeFlore </ORGANIZATION> said the $ 50,000 sanction against the firm should be thrown out because only LeFlore _ and not the firm _ signed key papers in the suit. <PERSON> LeFlore </PERSON> did not appeal to the high court to throw out the $ 50,000 penalty against him personally. The case is <ORGANIZATION> Pavelic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> LeFlore </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> vs. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marvel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION>, 88-791.
