<HEAD>Video View: Home Video Reviews</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` Poltergeist III'' -LRB- MGM-UA Home Video. VHS-Beta, $ 89.95. PG-13 -RRB- `` Poltergeist III'' should have had all the flaws of its predecessors _ cubed _ in the negative exponential fashion of <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION> sequels. It does n't. It's excellent. -LRB- Sadly, it was the last film for child star <PERSON> Heather </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Rourke </PERSON>, who died during surgery after the movie's theatrical release. -RRB- In this episode, the spirit world's demonic preacher <PERSON> Kane </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> -RRB- is again determined to get <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Anne </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Heather </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Rourke </PERSON> -RRB- to guide him `` into the light'' on the Other Side again. No problem; you would n't have it any other way. <PERSON> Tangina </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Zelda </PERSON> <PERSON> Rubinstein </PERSON> -RRB-, the chubby little medium from `` I'' and `` II'' returns to help <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Anne </PERSON>, along with the doughty <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Skerritt </PERSON> and <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON>, who play <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Anne </PERSON>'s devoted uncle and aunt. <PERSON> Skerritt </PERSON> is the manager of a sleek, mirrored high-rise building, the all-too familiar `` complex of shops, offices and apartments.'' So ... what if ... the evil spirit moves into the building? Why, it's ... an Eighties nightmare!!! The building becomes a stunning, surreal maze of endless-seeming stairwells, filled with mirrored walls with spectral images, with crazy elevators that go crazy and demonic cars in a frozen parking garage. Note that all the special effects were shot on-camera. Some of them are ingenious and utterly simple _ and awfully scary. Director <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Sherman </PERSON> could n't get all the originals' stars and could n't afford the costly opticals and other lab effects, so he and co-writer <PERSON> Brian </PERSON> <PERSON> Taggert </PERSON> went after something different and succeeded brilliantly. Aces. _ By <PERSON> Scott </PERSON> <PERSON> Williams </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 `` A Fish Called Wanda'' -LRB- CBS-Fox Video. VHS-Beta, $ 89.98. Rated R -RRB- One of the biggest box-office surprises of the season was `` A Fish Called <PERSON> Wanda </PERSON>,'' a juicy jewel heist romp starring <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Clease </PERSON> -LRB- who also wrote the screenplay -RRB- and <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Palin </PERSON> of `` Monty Python'' fame, <PERSON> Kevin </PERSON> <PERSON> Kline </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jamie </PERSON> <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Curtis </PERSON>. `` Wanda'' is the type of comedy we long to see but only get once every decade. It's wacky, sophisticated, obvious, raunchy, irreverent, delicious and a laugh a minute. <PERSON> George </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Georgeson </PERSON> -RRB-, Otto -LRB- <PERSON> Kline </PERSON> -RRB-, <PERSON> Wanda </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Curtis </PERSON> -RRB- and <PERSON> Ken </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Palin </PERSON> -RRB- pull a diamond heist and immediately set to double-triple cross each other. <PERSON> Wanda </PERSON> and <PERSON> Otto </PERSON> set up <PERSON> George </PERSON> and get him arrested for the crime. But before the cops take him off in cuffs, he hides the key to the safety deposit box in which the gems are hidden in <PERSON> Ken </PERSON>'s fish food. <PERSON> Ken </PERSON> finds the key and hides it in the treasure box in his beloved fish tank where his prize fish is an angel also named <PERSON> Wanda </PERSON>. Stay tuned for a tragic scene later in the movie featuring little <PERSON> Wanda </PERSON>. The only witness who can place <PERSON> George </PERSON> near the scene of the crime is a little old lady who owns three tiny dogs. <PERSON> Ken </PERSON> decides to kill her so she wo n't be able to testify. He misses three times. Go figure. But the bit, as cruel and crazy as it is, is also one of the funniest running gags on film. <PERSON> Cleese </PERSON> is <PERSON> George </PERSON>'s defense counsel, <PERSON> Archie </PERSON> <PERS