<TEXT>
 New figures show <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> members are complying with a new production accord designed to lift crude oil prices, a top official of the organization said. <PERSON> Subroto </PERSON>, secretary-general of the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exporting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Countries </ORGANIZATION>, said Monday crude prices would definitely reach the cartel's target of $ 18 a barrel in the second half of this year. According to figures released by <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION>, 12 of the countries supplied a total of 17.42 million barrels a day in January, slightly less than the quota of 17.51 million barrels set for them.
