<BYLINE>By RUTH RENDON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Computer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> announced Tuesday it no longer will market its products through <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> stores in the wake of a dispute with the huge retail chain. `` It has become apparent to us that continuing our relationship with <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION> is not in the best interest of <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION> or our customers,'' said <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Swavely </PERSON>, vice president of sales and marketing for Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION> last year accounted for about 7 percent of the $ 2.1 billion in annual revenue for <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION>, a leading maker of desktop, laptop and portable personsal computers. At the same time, sales of <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION> products accounted for about 15 percent of the $ 872 million in net sales during fiscal 1988 for <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION>, which is based in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jose </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Swavely </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION> had requested a business relationship in which the companies would have been `` strategic partners. <PERSON> Swavely </PERSON> said that would have required <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION> to give <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION> company preferential treatment, <PERSON> Swavely </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION> has n't given it and <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION> has elected not to support <ORGANIZATION> Compaq </ORGANIZATION>, he said. `` Simply put, <ORGANIZATION> Businessland </ORGANIZATION> has repeatedly requested special treatment that would give them an advantage over other authorized dealers. <ORGANIZATION> Compa